Package com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport Description

Contains classes and interfaces for communicating data with i2 Analyze services that interact with the Analysis Repository.

The basic constructs within the i2 Analyze data model are entities (which represent real-world objects), links (which represent associations between entities), and properties (which represent attributes of entities and links).

Items represent the common features of entities and links, which include the properties that both may have. In the Analysis Repository, properties are stored in cards, either alone or in related groups.

The API maps closely to the structure in the Analysis Repository. Items contain cards, which contain properties, property groups, provenance, and details about the source of the property values that they store. At the periphery, property groups also contain properties, and links store the identifiers of the entities that they connect.

Since:
1.0
